olive oil
2 potato
½ sachet sesame seeds
2 radish
1 cucumber
2 packet chicken breast
1 sachet Sweet Soy Seasoning
1 packet sweet chilli sauce
1 packet Mixed Salad Leaves
½ packet ponzu sauce
½ tsp sesame oil
1 packet Mayonnaise

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Cut potato into fries. Place on a lined oven tray. Season with salt, drizzle with olive oil, sprinkle over mixed sesame seeds (see ingredients) and toss to coat. Bake until tender, 20-25 minutes.
TIP: If your oven tray is crowded, divide between two trays.

• Meanwhile, thinly slice radish and cucumber.
• Place your hand flat on top of chicken breast and slice through horizontally to make two thin steaks. In a medium bowl, combine chicken, sweet soy seasoning and a drizzle of olive oil.

• When the fries have 10 minutes remaining, in a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over a medium-high heat. Add chicken steaks and cook until cooked through, 3-5 minutes each side (cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded). Remove pan from heat and add sweet chilli sauce, gently turning chicken to coat.
TIP: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink inside.

• While chicken is cooking, combine cucumber, radish, mixed salad leaves, ponzu sauce and the sesame oil in a large bowl. Season to taste.
• Divide sweet soy chicken, sesame fries, ponzu cucumber salad between plates. Serve with mayonnaise. Enjoy!